      • type

        byte type
        Type of key, as defined by "TYPE_" constants in this class.

      • first

        long first
        First 8B of the key data. Depending on type these bytes mean different things. Keeping the layout fixed and always 12B (these bytes plus 4B from second simplified some aspects of reading, writing and working with the data.

      • second

        int second
        Additional 4B of key data. Depending on type these bytes mean different things or are unused.
